{"name":"Scars Table","content":"<table style=\"width:99.1549%;height:244px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:48px\">\n<td style=\"width:99.7159%;height:48px\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>When an attack reduces a PC's HP to exactly 0, they are uniquely impacted. Look up the result on the table below based on the total damage taken.</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:10px\">\n<td style=\"width:99.7159%;height:4px;background-color:#000000\" colspan=\"2\"> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Just a scratch:  </strong>Take a scar. Roll <strong>1d6 </strong><em>[1: Neck, 2: Hands, 3: Eye, 4: Chest, 5: Legs, 6: Ear] <br /></em>If you rolled higher than your max HP, replace that with this new result.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Sucker Punch: </strong> Hit while you were distracted, you're left winded and a little shaken.<br />Roll <strong>1d6</strong>.  If you rolled higher than your max <strong>HP</strong>, replace that with this new result.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Wounded Pride:</strong>  You're put straight on your ass.  Angry, you get back up with a renewed <br />determination.  Roll <strong>3d6 </strong>and if higher than your <strong>CHA </strong>increase your <strong>CHA </strong>by <strong>+1</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Smashed Mouth:</strong>  You spit teeth and blood.  You look a complete mess and have <strong>Disadvantage</strong><em><strong> <br /></strong></em>on all <strong>CHA </strong>saves except intimidation, until you see a Dentist.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Bloody Mess: </strong> That will need stitches!  You are <strong>deprived </strong>until patched up by a Doctor.<br />Re-roll your Maximum <strong>HP </strong>on <strong>2d6 </strong>and keep the result if higher.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\">\n<p><strong>Maimed:</strong>  Part of you is torn off!  Roll <strong>1d6 </strong><em>[1: Nose, 2: Finger, 3: Eye, 4: Toe, 5: Thumb, 6: Ear]</em></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\">\n<p><strong>The Organ Trail: </strong> A vital organ is punctured. If you take Critical Damage before seeing a Doctor, you'll die.   If you get it seen to, re-roll your Max <strong>HP</strong> on <strong>2d6 </strong>and keep the result if higher.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Torn Limb: </strong>A random limb is torn off or in need of amputation.  The Judge will tell you which. Then, make a <strong>CHA </strong>save. If you pass, increase your max <strong>CHA</strong> by <strong>1d6</strong>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Hamstrung: </strong> You can barely move until you get serious help and rest.  After recovery, roll <strong>3d6</strong>. If the total is higher than your max <strong>REF</strong>, take the new result.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Shattered Ego: </strong> You are dealt a humiliating blow, one that will be hard to come back from.  If you achieve revenge, re-roll your Max <strong>HP</strong> on <strong>3d6 </strong>and keep the result if higher.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">11</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Mortal Wound: </strong> You are deprived and out of action. You die in one hour unless healed. Upon recovery, roll <strong>2d6</strong>. Take the new result as your max <strong>HP</strong>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:7.6672%;height:16px;text-align:center\">12</td>\n<td style=\"width:92.0487%;height:16px\"><strong>Dead Man Walking:</strong>  You shouldn't have survived that, but you’re not dead yet. If you fail your next save against Critical Damage you die horribly. If you pass, remove this effect and re-roll your Maximum <strong>HP </strong>on <strong>3d6 </strong>and keep the result if higher.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3Y78U4YwzkKohhXb":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ocDSLLcFX5FrSotz"}},"_id":"LrYs2njpI1bnV4ka"}
